item.title: 'The Sweetheart Dance'
item.description: The Sweetheart Dance is a popular, often competitive, category in many Native American powwows, usually featuring couples dancing together in traditional regalia to honor companionship and love. Often held around Valentine’s Day or as part of winter powwows, this special event celebrates partnership, with winners sometimes decided by crowd applause or judges.

15. Here is what my winter looks like. Show me yours! P.S. As a last post I wanted to share that I'm a game dev and I live in Eastern Europe. We have a history with authoritarianism and it's... downsides. I mean just look at how unintentionally oppressive our architecture looks. So I'm making a game inspired by the Stanley Milgram book Obedience to Authority. I guess the subject has always interested me: "Why do good people follow evil orders?" The game tests if you obey orders and how does your moral compass work (if at all). I invite you to check it out on Steam: https://store.steampowered.com/app/4394170/The_Milgram_Experiment_Demo

item.title: Kay Rose is where she belongs
item.description:
The longest cat resident of the Greater Huntsville Humane Society got flown to her new home in Colorado today. She’s been in a cage for year but has FINALLY found her forever home. She started at the foot of the bed, still a little energetic from her flight….
Worked her way up to the legs…
And has finally settled down on her new mama’s stomach. I’m not crying, YOU’RE crying!! Welcome home, Kay Rose!!
